translated: Lindell, Sven Fredrik Elias, bank director, Jönköping, born on April 17, 1890 in Jönköping, son of factory owner Henning L. and Augusta Söderström. Married on the 28th with Margit Tornberg. Children: Christer, born in 1929. Passed high school exams in Linköping in 1910 and economic exams at the Stockholm School of Economics in 1914. Employed at Sydsvenska Kredit AB in Jönköping from 1914-1916, in Malmö from 1917-1918, Direktion der Disconto GS in Berlin in 1916, Svenska Handelsbanken in Stockholm from 1918-1932, Banque Nationale de Crédit in Paris from 1921-1922, Capital State Savings Bank in Chicago from 1922-1923, Jönköping City and County Savings Bank since 1932, executive director there. Chairman of the board for Lindell's Weighing Factory AB, board member of Försäkrings AB Allmän Brand, Sparbanken Bank AB, Swedish Savings Banks Association, chairman of Småland and Öland Savings Banks Association, vice chairman of Sparfrämjande Förlag AB, chairman of Jönköping Property Owners Association, in Jönköping, Rotary Club, and in Swedish Economic Association's Jönköping district. Travelled to Denmark and Finland, Germany in 1916, 1922, 1930, 1945, 1946, and 1947, France and England in 1921-1922, Spain, Italy, and Switzerland in 1922, and to the USA in 1922-1923. Hobby: tennis. Received the Order of Vasa, Gold Medal from the Småland Sports Association in 1945, Jönköping AIK Merit Medal, Stockholm's Gymnastics Club Merit Medal, and the Swedish Gymnastics Association's Merit Medal in gold.
